<item>
            <title>[BOOKKEEPER-53] race condition of  outstandingMsgSet@SubscribeResponseHandler </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BOOKKEEPER-53</link>
                <project id="12311293" key="BOOKKEEPER">Bookkeeper</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;outstandingMsgSet is a Set, so it is not thread-safe. The detail is as below:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;MessageConsumeRetryTask is In a timer, so in timer thread, when the timer is up, it will cause a outstandingMsgSet add operation:&lt;br/&gt;
MessageConsumeRetryTask.run() -&amp;gt; outstandingMsgSet.add(message) -&amp;gt; outstandingMsgSet.add(message)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;At the same time, in other thread(maybe main thread), there may be other operations of this outstandingMsgSet:&lt;br/&gt;
MessageConsumeCallback.operationFinished() -&amp;gt; messageConsumed(Message message) -&amp;gt; outstandingMsgSet.remove(message);&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12520060">BOOKKEEPER-53</key>
            <summary>race condition of  outstandingMsgSet@SubscribeResponseHandler </summary>
